OL,3,CDad jailed after calling for mosques
OL,4,Cto be burned down in Facebook posts
OL,6,FThe judge added that it was aggravated
OL,7,Fbecause it took place during a
OL,8,F"particularly sensitive social
OL,9,Fclimate", adding: "I have come to the
OL,10,Fconclusion that appropriate punishment
OL,11,Fcan only be achieved by immediate
OL,12,Fcustody."
OL,14,FBoyce, of Pleasant View, Penrhiwfer,
OL,15,Fhad pleaded guilty to publishing
OL,16,Fthreatening material intending to stir
OL,17,Fup religious hatred, contrary to
OL,18,FSection 29C(1) of the Public Order Act
OL,19,F1986.
